FeedPackage.Description:
A .NET Redis client that uses a special syntax for easing LUA script invocation named "procedures". The interface is based on templated strings, allowing to execute custom defined server side procedures as regular Redis commands.
Executions are done through "channels", that in essence are virtual connections to Redis that support synchronous and asynchronous invocation.
Commands are multiplexed and pipelined. Subscription topics are aggregated. Just a pair of connections can handle thousand of channels.

The WebSocketListener class provides simple methods that listen for and accept incoming WebSocket connection requests asynchronously. It is a lightweight listener that follows the official RFC 6455 specification with an API very similar to the TcpListener class.
It supports secure connections and per message deflate compression.

utility classes available:
SimplePin: Abstract pin class encompassing its type, IOAttribute and IIOContainer
SpreadPin: Derive SimplePin and add non-generic ISpread
DiffSpreadPin: Derive SimplePin and add non-generic IDiffSpread
PinDictionaryDynamicNode: Abstract node class which wraps input and output pins in dictionary and manages IIOFactory bloated shenanigan for you
GenericInput: wrapper class for the INode interface so you can reference individual slices as objects with an int indexer.
FeedPackage.Summary: Utilities to ease dynamic and generic node development for VVVV
